Package: geoconnexr
Title: Discover, Crosswalk, and Package Geoconnex Water Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Kyle", "Onda", , "konda@lincolninst.edu", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: Tools for discovering water-data sites and datasets through the
    Geoconnex persistent identifier, reference feature, and knowledge graph
    infrastructure. Provides typed identifier crosswalk foundations, safe
    query-template assets, versioned contracts, and reproducible-procedure
    metadata for watershed data snapshots. The package is in an architecture
    spike stage; its protocol slices provide bounded, cache-aware PID
    resolution, fail-closed JSON-LD retrieval and expansion, tolerant
    diagnostic-producing Geoconnex profile parsing, and a native bounded OGC
    API Features reference client with a validated provider-gage PID crosswalk
    and checksum-pinned optional COMID/mainstem membership substrates. Custom
    polygon AOIs have bounded offline CRS84 recipe construction and
    integrity-checked hydration boundaries, and an internal closed-tree
    verifier checks manifest-relative snapshot integrity offline. A bounded
    internal catalog value object and creation-only catalog snapshot writer
    provide a deterministic offline packaging substrate, and an internal
    selection-only fetch plan binds catalog distributions to strict handler
    metadata without constructing requests or executing providers. A separate
    internal host preflight uses bounded direct metadata reads for selected
    optional-package versions without loading namespaces and never claims
    execution readiness. A host-independent internal value object records
    deterministic, redacted, policy-bound direct-CSV GET intents without
    allocating budgets or authorizing transport. A second host-independent
    internal boundary allocates explicit global physical-attempt and byte
    reservations, holds non-CSV shares, and emits bounded non-executable
    direct-CSV logical request plans without transport or parser execution.
    An offline response boundary validates one bounded caller-supplied
    direct-CSV response candidate while explicitly withholding provider
    provenance, budget consumption, parsing, transport, and execution claims.
    A strict offline UTF-8 CSV boundary then parses only those exact retained
    bytes into a bounded character-only result contract without loading an
    optional parser package or upgrading the caller-supplied provenance claim.
    An internal single-attempt executor can now run one selected direct-CSV
    request through the DNS-pinned package transport, validate and parse the
    provider response, and bind it to one charged redacted attempt ledger row.
    A bounded internal direct-CSV orchestrator adds deterministic sequential
    admission, continue-on-error execution, exact all-distribution status
    reconciliation, compact successful results, and a strict no-network dry
    run. An internal single-page OGC API Features handler now reuses one held
    all-handler reservation, rechecks its native symbol immediately before
    invocation, performs one DNS-pinned request, and binds strict GeoJSON-to-sf
    normalization to the charged attempt. A cross-handler orchestrator now
    schedules direct CSV, WQP Result, EDR position, and OGC requests in one
    global order with shared admission limits, isolated failures, compact
    evidence, and exact all-distribution status. The EDR slice binds one CRS84
    point, parameter, UTC interval, and CoverageJSON response to package-owned
    transport and strict offline normalization. Graph discovery, public catalog,
    remaining provider handlers, pagination, replay, and provider-data
    packaging remain under development.
